  "id": "dua-thabat-fil-amr",
  "title": "Allahumma inni as'aluka ath-Thabat",
  "source": "Sunan an-Nasa'i 1304, Ahmad (sahih)",
  "arabic": "اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَسْأَلُكَ الثَّبَاتَ فِي الْأَمْرِ وَالْعَزِيمَةَ عَلَى الرُّشْدِ وَأَسْأَلُكَ مُوجِبَاتِ رَحْمَتِكَ وَعَزَائِمَ مَغْفِرَتِكَ وَأَسْأَلُكَ شُكْرَ نِعْمَتِكَ وَحُسْنَ عِبَادَتِكَ وَأَسْأَلُكَ قَلْبَاً سَلِيمَاً وَلِسَانَاً صَادِقَاً وَأَسْأَلُكَ مِنْ خَيْرِ مَا تَعْلَمُ وَأَعُوذُ بِكَ مِنْ شَرِّ مَا تَعْلَمُ وَأَسْتَغْفِرُكَ لِمَا تَعْلَمُ إِنَّكَ أنْتَ عَلاَّمُ الْغُيُوبِ",
  "meaning": "O Allah, I ask You for steadfastness in my affairs and determination in following right guidance. I ask You for the means to deserve Your mercy and the resolve to attain Your forgiveness. I ask You for thankfulness for Your favor and excellence in worshipping You. I ask You for a sound heart and a truthful tongue. I ask You for the good You know, and I seek refuge in You from the evil You know, and I ask Your forgiveness for what You know. Truly You are the Knower of the unseen.",
